\f0  Backend Routes
\f1 \
\

\f0  1. KPI Router (\cf4 /api/kpi\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - \cf4 GET\cf2  \cf4 /api/kpi/summary\cf2  \'97 Runs SQL queries against the msc_cargo tables to compute current KPI values vs targets. Returns array
\f1 \

\f0   of \cf4 \{name,\cf2  \cf4 value,\cf2  \cf4 target,\cf2  \cf4 alert_threshold,\cf2  \cf4 status:\cf2  \cf4 "green"|"amber"|"red",\cf2  \cf4 trend\}\cf2 .
\f1 \
\

\f0  2. Genie Router (\cf4 /api/genie\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - \cf4 POST\cf2  \cf4 /api/genie/ask\cf2  \'97 Proxies to Genie Conversation API (start-conversation). Polls until result, returns SQL + data +
\f1 \

\f0  text_response.
\f1 \

\f0  - \cf4 POST\cf2  \cf4 /api/genie/followup\cf2  \'97 Follows up in existing conversation.
\f1 \

\f0  - Uses OBO auth pattern (forwards user's Bearer token to Databricks API).
\f1 \
\

\f0  3. Email Router (\cf4 /api/email\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - \cf4 POST\cf2  \cf4 /api/email/draft\cf2  \'97 Takes context (KPI data, Genie insight text) + recipient + subject, calls Foundation Model endpoint
\f1 \

\f0  to generate a professional email draft. Returns markdown-formatted email body.
\f1 \
\

\f0  4. Campaigns Router (\cf4 /api/campaigns\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - \cf4 GET\cf2  \cf4 /api/campaigns\cf2  \'97 Lists campaigns from dim_campaign table.
\f1 \

\f0  - \cf4 POST\cf2  \cf4 /api/campaigns/recommend\cf2  \'97 Takes campaign parameters (budget, segment, product), queries historical
\f1 \

\f0  fact_campaign_performance for channel ROI by similar campaigns, uses Foundation Model to recommend channel mix allocation.
\f1 \
\

\f0  Frontend Pages
\f1 \
\

\f0  Dashboard (\cf4 /dashboard\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - Grid of KPI cards (9 KPIs from the instructions)
\f1 \

\f0  - Each card: metric name, current value, target, visual indicator (green/amber/red)
\f1 \

\f0  - Click a card \uc0\u8594  navigates to Genie chat with pre-filled question about that KPI
\f1 \
\

\f0  Genie Chat (\cf4 /chat\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - Chat interface with message history
\f1 \

\f0  - Input field at bottom, messages above
\f1 \

\f0  - Shows SQL generated (collapsible), data tables, and text explanations
\f1 \

\f0  - Maintains conversation_id for follow-ups
\f1 \
\

\f0  Email Composer (\cf4 /email\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - Recipient, subject, and context fields
\f1 \

\f0  - "Import from Chat" button to pull last Genie insight as context
\f1 \

\f0  - "Generate Draft" button \uc0\u8594  calls backend Foundation Model
\f1 \

\f0  - Editable rich-text preview of generated email
\f1 \

\f0  - "Copy" button for clipboard
\f1 \
\

\f0  Campaign Planner (\cf4 /campaigns\cf2 )
\f1 \
\

\f0  - Form: name, product focus, target segment, budget, date range, channel selection
\f1 \

\f0  - "Get Recommendation" button \uc0\u8594  AI suggests channel budget allocation based on historical ROI
\f1 \

\f0  - Shows historical comparables from fact_campaign_performance
\f1 \

\f0  - "Save Draft" stores to local state (Lakebase in future)
\f1 \
\

