\f0  Implementation Phases
\f1 \
\

\f0  Phase 1: Scaffold (5 min)
\f1 \
\

\f0  - Run \cf4 apx\cf2  \cf4 init\cf2  to create the project skeleton
\f1 \

\f0  - Configure \cf4 app.yaml\cf2  and \cf4 databricks.yml
\f1 \cf2 \
\

\f0  Phase 2: Backend \'97 KPI + Genie (20 min)
\f1 \
\

\f0  - Implement \cf4 config.py\cf2  with env vars
\f1 \

\f0  - Implement \cf4 core.py\cf2  with OBO auth helper
\f1 \

\f0  - Implement \cf4 kpi.py\cf2  router with SQL queries for all 9 KPIs
\f1 \

\f0  - Implement \cf4 genie.py\cf2  router (proxy pattern from conversation.md)
\f1 \
\

\f0   Proposed Layout:
\f1 \
\

\f0   1. KPI Dashboard (top) \'97 Real-time cards showing each KPI vs target with red/amber/green status, pulled directly from the
\f1 \

\f0   msc_cargo tables via SQL. Click any card to drill into the Genie chat with a pre-filled question.
\f1 \

\f0   2. Genie Chat (center-left) \'97 Conversational analytics powered by the Genie Space backend. The brand manager asks "why is NPS
\f1 \

\f0   dropping in MEA?" and gets SQL-backed answers with charts. Conversation history persists per session.
\f1 \

\f0   3. Email Composer (center-right) \'97 Takes Genie insights and drafts stakeholder emails (e.g., "Summarize this NPS decline for
\f1 \

\f0   regional leadership"). Uses a Foundation Model endpoint to generate the draft, pre-populated with data context from the chat.
\f1 \

\f0   4. Campaign Planner (bottom) \'97 Form to define new campaigns (name, budget, channels, target segment, dates) with an AI advisor
\f1 \

\f0    that recommends channel mix based on historical performance from \cf4 fact_campaign_performance\cf2 . Saves drafts locally and can push
\f1 \

\f0    to a tracking table.
\f1 \
\

\f0   Key architecture tradeoff: A Streamlit app would be faster to build (2-3 days) but would feel like a prototype. The APX
\f1 \

\f0   approach (FastAPI + React) takes ~5 days but gives a production-quality SPA with proper routing, responsive layout, and smooth
\f1 \

\f0    UX between panels.
\f1 \
